Usage Instructions:
===================
You need to have the following packages installed on a linux machine:
-> libsdl2-dev
-> libglew-dev
-> libglm-dev

The makefile provided is for linux machine. 
To use the makefile, just run 'make build' to build, 'make' to compile and 'make run' to run.

Once the animation is running you can use:
-> The UP/DOWN Arrow keys to increase/decrease the speed of the rotation of the Earth and Moon around the Sun.
-> The RIGHT/LEFT Arrow keys to increase/decrease the speed of the rotation of the Moon around the Earth.
-> The S key to stop the animation and the R key to start the animation.
-> As an alternative, the SPACE key to start/stop the animation.


